cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for lung nodule classification using computed tomography (CT) scans. This involves analyzing the shape, size, density, and structure of the nodules. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses Residual Blocks and Non-Local Blocks for feature extraction, which are common in deep learning and machine learning research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves training and validation of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could also place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
